******
[2] Mexico (Hidalgo State): fatal
Date: Fri 20 May 2022
Source: The Yucatan Times [edited]
https://www.theyucatantimes.com/2022/05/3-year-old-boy-dies-at-la-raza-imss-hospital-in-mexico-city-apparently-due-to-a-suspected-case-of-acute-hepatitis/


The Hidalgo Health Secretariat confirmed that a 3-year-old minor suspected of acute hepatitis died at the La Raza hospital in Mexico City.

The health authorities are awaiting the results of the tests to determine if it was indeed a case of atypical acute hepatitis. So far, Pachuca reports 4 suspected cases of this disease of unknown origin.

The minor, from Tulancingo, Hidalgo, was transferred to Mexico City to wait for a transplant because his condition progressed rapidly and led to liver failure. In the country's capital, there are 4 possible causes of childhood hepatitis of unknown origin. Oliva López, Secretary of Health of Mexico City, reported that these are children under 8 years of age. "In the city, there are 4 that are being studied and in the country, the data was given yesterday, 17 May 2022, of 21 suspect cases, so we are of course monitoring it," explained López.

